    "Then, the classic assortment problem targeted at optimizing the expected revenue is denoted by",
    "In the above optimization problem (AOP), x ∈ {0, 1} n denotes the decision vari- able indicating which of the items i ∈ N are included in the offered assortment.",
    "The objective represents the expected revenue and sums up the expected revenue obtained by each item i.",
    "The expected revenue per item is obtained by multiplying the purchase probability p i (x) of the item with its revenue r i.",
    "The optimization prob- lem formulation is completed by a binary constraint ensuring that all values of x i are either 0 or 1."
  ],
